===Etymology===
{{Han compound|女|也|c1=s|c2=p|t1=female, woman|ls=psc}}. Originally a variant of [[姐]] ("elder sister"), later repurposed as a feminine third-person pronoun influenced by European languages. Linguist {{w|Liu Bannong}} is credited with coining this use around 1910s.<ref>[http://www.cuhk.edu.hk/ics/21c/issue/articles/136_1207034.pdf Bi Xinwei (畢新偉), 2013, 「她」字的來源與女性主體性——評《「她」字的文化史》(The Origins of "She" and Female Subjectivity: A Review of «The Cultural History of "She"»), 二十一世紀, p. 139]</ref>.

